This paper is about instance segmentation, which is a fundamental computer vision task, and proposes a new method called BlendMask that combines top-down and bottom-up approaches to improve mask prediction. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also involves deep learning techniques and model optimization, which are related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The proposed method can be applied to object detection and robotics, which are relevant to cs.RO (Robotics) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
